crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This script first navigates to the user's temporary directory. It then attempts to download a file named `apps.bin` from a remote HTTPS URL (`https://6kjhgj.secludingcurly.digital/apps.bin`) and save it locally as `update`. Following the download, the script attempts to remove all extended attributes from the `update` file, suppressing any potential errors from this action. Subsequently, it modifies the permissions of the `update` file to make it executable. Finally, the script executes the `update` file. Each step is conditionally executed, meaning a step only proceeds if the previous one was successful, except for the extended attribute removal which is designed to always report success regardless of the outcome.
